In this section we investigate how the frame size affects the performance measures including the normalized throughput of a network. Since the channel is noisy frame error rate increases with frame size. For studying the effect of the frame size, we compare the performance measures for the case when the size of frame payload is 100 B and the case when the size is 500 B (see

    Table 3

). We assume that every station which wins the medium is allowed to transmit just one data frame regardless of the frame size. That is, the TXOP value is set to 0 for all the access categories .
